      <input global="false" required="true">
        <description>Sample items xml: 

&lt;items&gt;
	&lt;item&gt;
		&lt;operation-name&gt;restart-scheduler&lt;/operation-name&gt;
		&lt;scheduler-name&gt;sch1&lt;/scheduler-name&gt;
	&lt;/item&gt;
	
	&lt;item&gt;
		&lt;operation-name&gt;restart-scheduler&lt;/operation-name&gt;
		&lt;scheduler-name&gt;sch2&lt;/scheduler-name&gt;
	&lt;/item&gt;
	
	&lt;item&gt;
		&lt;operation-name&gt;restart-scheduler&lt;/operation-name&gt;
		&lt;scheduler-name&gt;&lt;/scheduler-name&gt;
	&lt;/item&gt;
	
	&lt;item&gt;
		&lt;operation-name&gt;restart-scheduler&lt;/operation-name&gt;
	&lt;/item&gt;
	
&lt;/items&gt;

Elements' Description

item [Required]: This is a child of items element. Within this element you can specify the name of the scheduler you want to restart. The item element can be used multiple time to restart more than one scheduler at the same time.

operation-name [Optional]: the operation to be performed.

Valid value: restart-scheduler
Default value: restart-scheduler

Note: this tag is 'Required' tag while executing request from CRUD level wrapper 'Perform Action'. 

scheduler-name [Optional]: Specifies the name of the scheduler you want to restart. If you do not specify this element within the &lt;item&gt; tag, the default scheduler is restarted. This tag is relevant for 'Windows' opeating system only. For other operating systems we don't need to specify the scheduler name.

Valid value: Any valid scheduler name.

Default value: TSM Client Scheduler(Only for Windows OS)</description>
        <from>items</from>
